Enterprise Multi-Area OSPF & Advanced Infrastructure Lab
Welcome to the Advanced Enterprise Network Simulation Lab. This project demonstrates a highly available, scalable, and secure enterprise network topology integrating Layer 2 redundancy, Layer 3 multi-area routing, and granular traffic filtering.

📌 Network Topology
Below is the network design used for this lab simulation (Referenced from Screenshot from 2026-06-29 11-14-18.png):

🛠️ Implemented Technologies & Protocols
1. Layer 2 Infrastructure & Redundancy
VLANs & Trunking: Broadcast domain separation and 802.1Q trunking across Access and Distribution layers.

EtherChannel: Link aggregation (LACP/PAgP) between switches to increase bandwidth and provide link redundancy.Ds1 and Ds2 between L3 Etherchannel bes int e1/2 down Neighbor between with portchannel-10.

Spanning Tree Protocol (MST): Multiple Spanning Tree (MST) implementation to optimize load-balancing per group of VLANs and prevent Layer 2 loops.

2. First Hop Redundancy Protocols (FHRP)
HSRP (Hot Standby Router Protocol): Active/Standby gateway redundancy deployed in the Left Segment (VLAN 2020 - 2023).

VRRP (Virtual Router Redundancy Protocol): Master/Backup open-standard gateway redundancy deployed in the Right Segment (VLAN 10 - 13).

3. Layer 3 Routing & OSPF Multi-Area Design
OSPF Area 0 (Core): Central Core Switch (CS) connecting all multi-area boundaries.network type with P2P.

OSPF Area Types (LSA Tuning):



Area 1 and 2 (Totally Stubby): Restricting all summary and external LSAs (Type 3, 4, 5) .

Area 5 & Area 6 (Virtual-Link): Transit area handling via OSPF Virtual-Link to connect Area 6 (DMZ-Zone) back to Area 0.

LSA Type Mastery: Verification and filtering of LSA Types 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, and 7 across the topology.

Default Route & WAN: Static default routing injected from R1/R2 to Multi-homed ISPs.

4. Advanced Traffic Engineering & Policy Filtering
Access Control Lists (ACLs): Infrastructure protection, securing SSH access across all devices, and managing IT Department policies.

Prefix-Lists: Exact network matching based on prefix length for routing updates and Default route Only.

Distribute-Lists: Filtering inbound/outbound routing updates inside OSPF processes.
By the Way !
This lab is in highly Redundancy and Traffic Engineering with using cost or bandwidth can be use changeable metric (E1/E2 or cost and Bandwidth)

